        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-09-15T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-09-15T21:00:00-05:00" n="730" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d730">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.0093/9–1648: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-09-16T11:00:00+09:00">September 16, 1948—11 a. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 16—1:16 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1702. Redeptel 1302, September 13, 3 p. m. Appropriate instructions have been
                    issued to Consulates. Embassy is most appreciative of Department’s explanation
                    of action which was not clear to Embassy and of the reasons, therefore, of which
                    it was not previously aware.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
